<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN and Judith Michaelson, Arts and entertainment reports from 
The Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese may soon be getting a look at Madonna. Promoters are trying to 
arrange a tour for the Material Girl this spring, which would make her the 
first American pop star to sing in the People's Republic, China Youth News 
reported. The newspaper said negotiations are under way between mainland China 
promoters and agents in Hong Kong for the singer to arrange the tour. Last 
year, Shanghai promoters were reported to be negotiating with agents for 
Michael Jackson to arrange a tour for him but nothing came of it. ALEENE 
MacMINN and Judith Michaelson 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Madonna 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
