<P>
Pakistan successfully has test-fired its first long-range, surface-to-surface 
missiles, its army chief, Gen. Mirza Aslam Beg, said. Quoted by the official 
Associated Press of Pakistan, Beg told military officers that two versions of 
the missiles, with a range of 185 miles and 50 miles respectively, were tested 
