<HEADLINE>
<P>
JEWISH FUND DRIVE $1 MILLION OVER GOAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Jewish Federation Council of Greater Los Angeles' United Jewish Fund 
surpassed its fund-raising target by $1 million Sunday as more than 5,000 
volunteer telephone solicitors received pledges for $4 million during the 
12-hour campaign, council officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Called "Super Sunday," the campaign raised money to fund a broad range of 
health, education, welfare and social service programs in Los Angeles, Israel 
and other parts of the world. 
</P>
<P>
Campaign officials said a "significant" amount of the money raised will be used 
to help pay resettlement costs for between 3,000 and 5,000 Soviet Jews expected 
to arrive in the Southland this year. 
</P>
