<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SUN VALLEY MAN, 78, FOUND AFTER 2 DAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 78-year-old Sun Valley man who had been missing since Friday was found Sunday 
night afterhe called a friend's home. 
</P>
<P>
Bruce William McEntire looked about "an inch from being homeless" when he was 
found at Tampa Avenue and Roscoe Boulevard, according to his son, Chuck 
McEntire. He had spent the last two days doing "a lot of driving and sitting in 
his car", said his daughter, Nancy McEntire. 
</P>
<P>
Bruce McEntire called a friend, Sherree Herts, after looking up her number in 
the phone book about 9 p. m. Herts kept him on the phone while Chuck McEntire 
went to fetch him. 
</P>
<P>
McEntire has been losing his memory and growing disoriented in recent years, 
said Nancy McEntire. McEntire, a crossing guard at Noble Avenue School in 
Sepulveda, has been living with his daughter since Jan.1. 
</P>
<P>
He had last been seen Friday about 9 p.m. driving on Nordhoff Street in 
Northridge, following his estranged wife in another car after they had had 
dinner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
