<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: AZTECS SPLIT DOUBLEHEADER WITH FLORIDA 
INTERNATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego State baseball team split a doubleheader with Florida 
International University Sunday at Smith Field, winning the first game, 5-4, 
and losing the second, 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
Billy Miller scored the game-winning run for the Aztecs (3-1) in the first 
game, coming home from second on an error in the seventh. Dave Riddle (1-0) 
picked up the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Florida International (5-2) took a 4-0 lead in the second game and held on to 
win after allowing the Aztecs three unearned runs in the sixth. Paul Anderson 
was the winning pitcher, John Marshall (0-1) the loser. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. International (2-2) split a doubleheader at UCLA, winning the first game, 
4-1, and losing the second, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
USIU's Mike Ronberg (2-0) pitched a four-hitter in the first game. Beto 
Rodriguez was three for four for the Gulls, including a two-run home run in the 
third. 
</P>
<P>
USIU's Steve Kreger hit his third home run of the season in the second game, 
but UCLA improved to 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
SDSU's Tole Marinkovic defeated Robert Soneru, 2-6, 6-4, 6-1, to help the host 
Aztecs (1-4) defeat U.S. International, 7-2. 
</P>
<P>
After losing the first set, Marinkovic was down, 3-1, in the second set before 
coming back. The Aztecs won matches at the No. 4 through 6 singles positions 
before sweeping doubles. 
</P>
<P>
FOOTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma High School's John Louis, a 6-foot-1, 170 pound cornerback, has 
orally committed to San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
"I think he fits into their system very well," Point Loma Coach Bennie Edens 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Louis also considered Oregon, Stanford, Colorado and Arizona State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
