</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MILAN, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police have arrested a woman who forced her 13-year-old daughter into 
prostitution, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Two others arrested were a 36-year-old man who had paid for sex with the girl 
for the past four years and a woman who acted as an intermediary. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the operation, which came to light during an investigation of a 
murder in the area, ended last week when they raided the house where the 
encounters took place and found the man with the girl. 
</P>
<P>
They said the man, a local businessman, had been paying the girl's mother, 
herself a prostitute, and the woman intermediary to film the girl or have sex 
with her since she was 9 years old. 
</P>
